1
00:00:24,316 --> 00:00:28,529
[REN] I've had the same dream
every night. Without fail.

2
00:00:32,658 --> 00:00:36,703
[REN] And when I wake up,
someone is dead.

3
00:00:36,787 --> 00:00:40,249
Beheaded. As if
by a guillotine.

4
00:00:46,713 --> 00:00:48,465
That's just crazy.

5
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:51,176
[KASUMI sighs] How'd I
know you'd be up here?

6
00:00:51,260 --> 00:00:52,594
Uh...

7
00:00:52,678 --> 00:00:55,305
Come on. Just because you
don't want to go to class,

8
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:58,433
doesn't mean you
don't have to go.

9
00:00:58,517 --> 00:00:59,893
Light blue. And white.

10
00:00:59,977 --> 00:01:00,561
[REA, KASUMI]
Hm?

11
00:01:00,644 --> 00:01:01,979
[REN]
Thank you.

12
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:04,022
[camera snaps]

13
00:01:04,106 --> 00:01:06,066
[REA, KASUMI gasp]

14
00:01:06,149 --> 00:01:11,947
[KASUMI growls] What the hell do
you think you're doing? Asshole!

15
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:19,413
♪

16
00:02:51,672 --> 00:02:56,009
[KASUMI] Ugh! You're perverted,
rude, and worse, stupid!

17
00:02:56,093 --> 00:02:58,595
You're just awful!
You should be ashamed.

18
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,181
Enough already, you've been
chewing me out for blocks.

19
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:03,517
That's what I was greeted with
when I looked up so I took

20
00:03:03,600 --> 00:03:05,769
the opportunity to
immortalize the moment.

21
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:08,855
Oh yeah? Well, I took the
opportunity to kick your ass.

22
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:11,149
You did delete
the picture, didn't you?

23
00:03:11,233 --> 00:03:12,401
Probably.

24
00:03:12,484 --> 00:03:13,610
What do you mean by "probably?"

25
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:14,569
[WOMAN A]
Pervert!

26
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:17,781
[VALERIA grunts]
No. Forgive me.

27
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:21,660
You have it all wrong, miss.
I mean you no harm.

28
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:22,911
I merely needed direct‐‐

29
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:24,955
[WOMAN A] No! I told you
to keep away from me!

30
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:28,875
‐‐[thudding]
‐‐[VALERIA grunting]

31
00:03:28,959 --> 00:03:31,169
[REN] Wow. I suppose
we should expect to see

32
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:33,171
more of this kind of
stuff at a time like this.

33
00:03:33,255 --> 00:03:34,840
Being approached
by a suspicious man,

34
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:37,843
with all these murders happening
in town. I can't blame her.

35
00:03:37,926 --> 00:03:39,720
Hey, are you all right?

36
00:03:39,803 --> 00:03:40,637
Whoa, hang on!

37
00:03:40,721 --> 00:03:43,014
[VALERIA grunts]

38
00:03:43,098 --> 00:03:44,182
Do you need some help?

39
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:47,894
[VALERIA grunts]
A‐Apologies.

40
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,230
I'm okay... now.

41
00:03:53,233 --> 00:03:54,901
You're really tall.

42
00:03:54,985 --> 00:03:57,821
Come on. Get out
of the man's way.

43
00:03:57,904 --> 00:04:00,282
Pardon me, do you think you
could tell me which way

44
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:03,076
to go to get to the church?

45
00:04:03,160 --> 00:04:04,828
[KASUMI] Hey, Father,
do you know Rea?

46
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,622
She's a friend of ours from
school who stays at the church.

47
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:11,001
[VALERIA] Ja, but I haven't
been here in almost a decade.

48
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:13,128
The town's changed
so much since then.

49
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:14,838
I imagine she has too.

50
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,966
I can't tell you how relieving
it is to hear that dear Theresia

51
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:20,719
has such good friends at
school as the two of you kids!

52
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:22,053
Out of all the upperclassmen,

53
00:04:22,137 --> 00:04:24,806
Himuro's always been
the coolest to us.

54
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:27,017
When we first met her she told
us to just call her Rea,

55
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,519
but I guess "Theresia"
must be her real name?

56
00:04:29,603 --> 00:04:32,063
I think she's actually,
what, a quarter Japanese?

57
00:04:32,147 --> 00:04:35,358
[VALERIA] Indeed! And I
was the one who named her.

58
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:36,693
[KASUMI]
Oh, that's cool.

59
00:04:36,777 --> 00:04:39,070
So that means you're sort
of like Rea's dad, huh?

60
00:04:39,154 --> 00:04:43,074
[VALERIA laughs] Oh my,
how very embarrassing!

61
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:45,660
But, ja, I suppose
that's accurate.

62
00:04:45,744 --> 00:04:47,454
I changed her diaper
countless times,

63
00:04:47,537 --> 00:04:50,582
and gave her baths as well.
And I also made a promise

64
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,834
to do everything in my
power to protect her!

65
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:54,628
I do it all for
the sake of love!

66
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:58,757
Theresia! Oh!
Mein kleines knuddelbar!

67
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:01,760
Daddy dearest has finally
made his way back to you!

68
00:05:01,843 --> 00:05:02,886
[REA]
Creepy.

69
00:05:02,969 --> 00:05:03,929
[VALERIA grunts]

70
00:05:05,764 --> 00:05:09,351
It's time for you to hit
the bricks. Or better yet, die.

71
00:05:09,434 --> 00:05:11,895
[VALERIA shouts] Theresia!

72
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:15,565
When did your tender eyes
grow as cold as a graveyard?

73
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:18,193
[VALERIA] No. I like them.
The new look works!

74
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:19,945
[KASUMI]
Okay.

75
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:22,239
[REN] What are we supposed
to do with this weirdo?

76
00:05:24,241 --> 00:05:25,325
[RIZA]
Ahem.

77
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:27,077
It's been a while since
our last meeting,

78
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,620
and though hard to believe,

79
00:05:28,703 --> 00:05:30,872
the subtext of your speech has
grown even more disturbing.

80
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:33,583
So, Father Trifa, are you
trying to get banished

81
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:35,293
to the Mexican
countryside again?

82
00:05:35,377 --> 00:05:37,963
[VALERIA gasps]

83
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:40,090
Riza?

84
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:41,967
You two must be
famished after dealing

85
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:44,094
with the Father's nonsense.

86
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:47,138
As an apology, I'd love to
whip up some food for you!

87
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:03,196
[REN] It's starting to
get late, so we'd better go.

88
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:05,115
Thank you for the
delicious meal.

89
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:07,200
[RIZA] And thank you
for your help today.

90
00:06:07,284 --> 00:06:09,327
Father Trifa can be
quite a handful.

91
00:06:09,411 --> 00:06:10,704
[REN]
Glad to help.

92
00:06:10,787 --> 00:06:12,956
Especially when I get
repaid with such great food.

93
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:15,292
[RIZA]
You think so? But still,

94
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:18,169
I'm sure it can't be as good
as Kasumi's home cooking.

95
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:21,089
Nah. She can be kinda
lazy sometimes,

96
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,465
and she doesn't make
anything special, so‐‐

97
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:26,511
[RIZA] Uh‐uh! You shouldn't
say that so cavalierly.

98
00:06:26,595 --> 00:06:29,598
And if trying to flatter someone
is your actual intention,

99
00:06:29,681 --> 00:06:32,309
you need to pick a
different someone than me.

100
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:33,852
For example.

101
00:06:33,935 --> 00:06:37,564
Tell me, Ren. You don't know
Rea's birthday, do you?

102
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:39,566
It's coming up soon
on the twenty‐fifth.

103
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:41,526
She was born on Christmas Day!

104
00:06:41,610 --> 00:06:43,028
Wow, is that true?

105
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:45,488
Riza, please mind
your own business.

106
00:06:45,572 --> 00:06:47,699
I don't want to hear
you talking about it.

107
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:50,702
[RIZA]
Ja, ja, I understand. I'm sorry!

108
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:52,954
She's so shy, it's adorable.

109
00:06:55,457 --> 00:06:58,001
[REN grunts]
So, yeah. Christmas.

110
00:06:59,836 --> 00:07:01,504
I'd like to maybe
get you a present,

111
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:03,381
if that's okay with you.

112
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:08,595
Sure. Thanks a lot.
That's so sweet.

113
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:10,639
[REN]
Uh?

114
00:07:10,722 --> 00:07:12,098
We should get married.

115
00:07:12,182 --> 00:07:14,142
[VALERIA] Theresia! What did
you just say, young lady?

116
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:15,352
That's too forward!

117
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:16,603
[RIZA] She has to
grow up sometime,

118
00:07:16,686 --> 00:07:18,355
so just knock it off!

119
00:07:22,359 --> 00:07:25,403
I had a great time!
See you tomorrow, Rea!

120
00:07:25,487 --> 00:07:27,697
[REA]
Yeah. Take care.

121
00:07:32,994 --> 00:07:34,579
[VALERIA]
Fujii, wait.

122
00:07:34,663 --> 00:07:36,289
[REN]
Hm?

123
00:07:36,373 --> 00:07:39,960
Pardon us. I had a question I
wanted to ask him in private.

124
00:07:40,043 --> 00:07:41,211
[KASUMI]
Mm‐hm.

125
00:07:43,004 --> 00:07:46,299
[VALERIA] You and Miss Ayase.
Were you both born here?

126
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:49,219
[REN] No, we weren't.
Why do you ask?

127
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:51,554
Ah. You must be worried
about the recent spate

128
00:07:51,638 --> 00:07:53,390
of murders occurring in town.

129
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,642
And you think we should move
out to the country until this

130
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,185
all blows over, don't you?

131
00:07:57,268 --> 00:07:59,479
Ja, am I that easy to read?

132
00:07:59,562 --> 00:08:02,107
And what about your parents,
Mister Fujii?

133
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,566
My parents?

134
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:07,362
[REN]
Well...

135
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:09,114
My mother and father
both passed away

136
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:10,699
when I was a still
a little boy.

137
00:08:10,782 --> 00:08:13,535
Kasumi's family took me in after
that and raised me like a son.

138
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:15,829
And sadly, just a
couple of years ago,

139
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:18,415
we lost Kasumi's father.

140
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:22,335
[VALERIA]
Oh, I see. My condolences.

141
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:23,712
Now then.

142
00:08:23,795 --> 00:08:26,423
I can only imagine how badly
you'd like to meet them.

143
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,383
Do you mean meet the dead?

144
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:36,558
[KASUMI] It's freezing
out here. Can we go?!

145
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:40,103
That's impossible.
Once you die, it's over.

146
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,896
You don't get to come back.

147
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,149
That's why the here and
now is so important,

148
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:47,402
and I think anyone who can't
understand that is crazy.

149
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:52,991
[VALERIA] Of course.
You're absolutely right.

150
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:55,994
That does sound crazy,
doesn't it?

151
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,705
Did you hear that? Leonhart?

152
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:00,540
[KEI]
Yes.

153
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:03,960
[VALERIA] And what do you think
of that young man's opinion?

154
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:08,214
I'm not bothered. A person is
free to have their thoughts.

155
00:09:08,298 --> 00:09:12,469
Ah. In other words, you didn't
find what he said upsetting?

156
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:18,975
[laughs] How frightening.
I joke, of course.

157
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:21,352
But then, Shambhala
has always been a place

158
00:09:21,436 --> 00:09:24,272
where the crazy are
born and converge.

159
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:28,276
Correct or not, if someone
falls into its grand net,

160
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:30,904
they'll be tested.

161
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:33,239
I'll allow you to make the
decisions on the ground,

162
00:09:33,323 --> 00:09:35,158
for now.

163
00:09:35,241 --> 00:09:37,994
And I will be able to
adapt as I see fit?

164
00:09:38,078 --> 00:09:41,498
Whatever you command of me,
O Priest of the Grail.

165
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:52,425
Huh. Oh, my, what do
we have here?

166
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:59,849
I suspect you might be another
toy of our vice commander's.

167
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:01,559
You poor thing.

168
00:10:11,486 --> 00:10:16,491
[REN grunts]

169
00:10:22,247 --> 00:10:27,168
[grunting contiues]

170
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:40,557
[footsteps]

171
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:45,603
[WOMAN A pants]

172
00:10:48,857 --> 00:10:51,234
[WOMAN A gasps]

173
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:01,077
[REN gasps]

174
00:11:07,959 --> 00:11:12,881
[REN gasps, vomits]

175
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:21,973
[pants] No way. This can't
be happening! I didn't...

176
00:11:22,056 --> 00:11:26,519
It wasn't me. It wasn't me!
I didn't do it!

177
00:11:26,603 --> 00:11:30,982
[WILHELM] Your taste in prey
is excellent. I am impressed.

178
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:33,359
[REN]
H‐Huh?

179
00:11:39,407 --> 00:11:40,617
[WILHELM]
Looks like your reflexes

180
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,410
are rather sharp as well.

181
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:45,163
I am extremely fortunate
to have found you.

182
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,998
[REN gasps]

183
00:11:47,081 --> 00:11:48,958
You going to just
stand around staring?

184
00:11:49,042 --> 00:11:51,753
You are able to speak,
aren't you?

185
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:53,838
[REN gasps]

186
00:11:53,922 --> 00:11:54,672
[RUSALKA]
Ha!

187
00:11:54,756 --> 00:11:56,007
[REN shouts]

188
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:59,594
Hey! Trying to run isn't
going to get you very far.

189
00:12:02,347 --> 00:12:03,765
[REN gasps]

190
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:07,393
[RUSALKA] My, my! This little
one is quite interesting!

191
00:12:07,477 --> 00:12:11,064
It's almost as if he's actually
trying to resist my Nachzehrer.

192
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,483
[WILHELM]
So? What do we do, Malleus?

193
00:12:13,566 --> 00:12:14,734
Want to play with him?

194
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:16,778
[RUSALKA]
Ah! Hold on.

195
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:20,073
You are the one that Mercurius
sent to us, are you not?

196
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:21,991
Did he give you some
kind of message?

197
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:23,618
Hu, what?

198
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:25,578
[RUSALKA]
Does Karl Krafft ring a bell?

199
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:28,414
The hooded,
mercurian mystery man?

200
00:12:29,916 --> 00:12:31,417
You've seen him, haven't you?

201
00:12:31,501 --> 00:12:34,128
And you did this because
he compelled you to.

202
00:12:34,212 --> 00:12:38,341
[REN] No! I don't know anything!
I didn't kill her!

203
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:39,384
[WILHELM]
Buffoon.

204
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:42,136
[REN grunts]

205
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:48,476
[WILHELM] I'm only going to
ask you this one more time.

206
00:12:48,559 --> 00:12:50,979
You sliced her head off,
did you not?

207
00:12:51,062 --> 00:12:53,439
Because that shitheel
Mercurius told you to.

208
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:58,152
[REN grunts, shouts]

209
00:12:58,236 --> 00:13:01,364
[WILHELM] Ja, that's right,
you know how I like to have fun!

210
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:04,367
And if you're faking it,
I'm sold anyway.

211
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:07,328
But I'm not the patient type,
I get bored quite easily.

212
00:13:07,412 --> 00:13:10,081
And if I think you're holding
out on me, then well,

213
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:12,542
I might not wait
for your answer.

214
00:13:12,625 --> 00:13:15,503
[shouts]

215
00:13:15,586 --> 00:13:19,007
Get your filthy claws
off me, you vermin.

216
00:13:19,090 --> 00:13:24,053
[REN grunts]

217
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,139
[WILHELM]
Last chance.

218
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:28,933
You murdered her,
isn't that right?

219
00:13:29,017 --> 00:13:32,228
[REN groans]

220
00:13:32,312 --> 00:13:33,688
I'm getting sick of this.

221
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:36,733
Okay, Malleus.
I'm going to kill him.

222
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:41,446
[sighs] How did I know
that you would say that?

223
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:45,158
Fine. Do as you will.
Always so predictable.

224
00:13:45,241 --> 00:13:47,493
I suppose torture is
too delicate of a task

225
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:49,954
to expect out of you.

226
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:53,916
But please, do try not to
mangle the head too much.

227
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,836
I should still be able
to use it, if I have to.

228
00:13:56,919 --> 00:14:00,465
Sure. I'll see if I
can restrain myself.

229
00:14:01,716 --> 00:14:04,677
[REN] What is this?
What's happening?

230
00:14:04,761 --> 00:14:08,264
I'm so confused.
What's going on?

231
00:14:09,432 --> 00:14:15,730
[REN] I killed that woman?
But why? I don't understand.

232
00:14:17,065 --> 00:14:19,359
[REN] And who the hell
are these people?

233
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:22,320
What do they want from me?

234
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:24,030
Time to die.

235
00:14:25,406 --> 00:14:27,533
[REN]
He's gonna kill me.

236
00:14:27,617 --> 00:14:29,911
No... No!

237
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:33,373
Show me the path I was
meant to tread upon.

238
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:34,415
[REN gasps]

239
00:14:39,879 --> 00:14:40,922
Oh?

240
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:42,465
